In a related development, a pastor, Joseph Anthony of Living Faith Church at Njaba LGA of Imo state was arrested for allegedly defiling a minor, aged 11 years. The victim, according to reports, was said to be the daughter of a fellow pastor, Chukwuma Okoronkwo who accommodated him in their house. CP Akinmoyede said the command has embarked on a full-scale investigation to fish out other criminals in the state, adding that the suspects would soon be charged to court. Meanwhile, items recovered from the suspects were 4 AK47 riffles, one LAR riffle, one SMG, 120 rounds of 7.62mm ammunition, three motorbikes, one Lexus 330 SUX and a total sum of 4million 200 thousand naira cash.